.TH "lookup_bdev" 9 "lookup_bdev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lookup_bdev \- lookup a struct block_device by name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lookup_bdev
.BI "(const char *pathname "  ","
.BI "dev_t *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pathname" 12
special file representing the block device
.IP "dev" 12
return value of the block device's dev_t
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Get a reference to the blockdevice at \fIpathname\fP in the current
namespace if possible and return it.  Return ERR_PTR(error)
otherwise.
